article.description: — Drake Allen scored 17 points as Southern Utah beat Division III-member La Verne 117-55 on Thursday.
article.headline: Southern Utah crushes D III-member La Verne 117-55
article.linkText: Southern Utah crushes D III-member La Verne 117-55
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Drake Allen scored 17 points as Southern Utah beat Division III-member La Verne 117-55 on Thursday. Allen made all eight of his shots from the floor for the Thunderbirds (1-1). Harrison Butler recorded 16 points and was 5 of 10 shooting, including 2 for 4 from distance, and went 4 for 5 from the line. Brian Adams, John Malone II and Taveres James all scored eight for the Leopards. NEXT UP Southern Utah hosts Saint Katherine in its next matchup on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
